(l) Pigge is a Grower name, but John Pigge was of Whstewell, a place near Carnllwyd, unless, indeed there be another in Gower.

(2) Hugh Bassett was a younger son of John Bassett of St. Hilary, from whom he inherited the de la Bere lands in Gower, which he forfeited for killing Sir Thomas de ap Grono. They were granted to Sir Rhys ap Thomas, then reverted to the Crown, and finally were granted to the Earl of Pembroke.
